st of all, I have to explain (yet again) TWC policy as far as it would have applied in that case.  Maybe some have heard of it, its commonly known as FiF.  Two parts: first and in force.  Ultimately the only demonstration of proper &quot;force that is there first&quot; is pulling and killing a mob before anyone else does.  However our policy is that if another raid force is there before us and if and only if, in OUR judgement based off OUR experience, they have a force that is likely able to beat that mob, then we will leave and let them kill it as they would even if we think they have a chance at failure and might need one or more wipes/retries.  If we do not think they have enough of a force, based on what we think/know we would need, or it isnt clear who was there decidedly &quot;first&quot; then its back to the &quot;who pulls and kills first&quot; scenerio.<br>
<br>
From what I understand of this Idol/AoW thing, the TWC officers present had no idea that GoL and Fam were actually raiding together.  I would imagine it looked more like one of them (Fam?) killing statue with forces that were probably not adequate to kill AoW, and then the other (GoL?) comming late to attempt the same mob on their own.  If they had seen what they thought was an inadequate force (Fam in this case in their opinion at that time) stalling they would eventually go ahead and pull, and apparently that's what they did.<br>
<br>
So lets go over things again in an abstract sense and really dig down into the minds of those baby-eating TWC bastards:<br>
<br>
- Statue is up.  This means AoW is a possible target.<br>
- Go to Kael, see Fam there.<br>
- Fam has force and is there first for Statue -&gt; TWC sits there and waits while Fam kills statue.<br>
- GoL entering zone.  They aren't first that's for sure -&gt; TWC ignores them.<br>
- Fam probably doesnt have enough for AoW -&gt; TWC no leave zone<br>
- Being that we're so freaking nice and all and given they they did meet half the requirements, being there first, we give them time to prove that their present force is in fact strong enough to kill AoW -&gt; Tell them they have X amount of time.<br>
- Time passes, their force which we suspected wasnt strong enough in the first place hasn't tried to engage yet -&gt; TWC pulls<br>
